text: Retail sales remain unchanged from January 2024, according to a first estimate.
analysis question: What is the trend in retail sales from January 2024?
analysis operation: calculate the monthly sales figures to identify any changes
logic description: As there are no previous segments, this analysis question is the initial question derived from the dataset to understand the sales trend for retail sales starting from January 2024.

text: Sales volumes and values broadly unchanged in February 2024
February 2024 was a steadier month as sales values (amount spent) fell marginally by 0.1%, alongside unchanged volumes.
However, volumes fell 0.4% over the year and remained 1.3% below their pre-coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic level in February 2020. These data are available in our Retail Sales Index datasets.
analysis question: What are the trends in retail sales volume and value in February 2024, and how do they compare with the previous year and pre-pandemic levels?
analysis operation: compare the monthly sales figures volume and value to identify changes over time and compared to previous periods
logic description: The analyst is now focusing on February 2024, a different time period from the initial analysis, to understand how retail sales have evolved from the previous month and also compared to the previous year and pre-pandemic levels.

text: Clothing store sales increase following falls in previous months

Food stores sales volumes fell by 0.3% over the month following January's recovery from December's record fall in 2023. Respondents again reported poor weather leading to a reduction in footfall, consistent with footfall measures in our Economic activity and social change in the UK, real-time indicators bulletin.
Automotive fuel sales volumes fell by 1.3% over the month to February 2024 as fuel prices increased slightly. For more information on fuel prices, see GOV.UK's Weekly road fuel prices tables.
analysis question: How did the volume sales changes for different retail categories in February 2024?
analysis operation: visualize the monthly percentage changes in volume sales for the different categories of retail for February 2024
logic description: The segment is delving into detailed category-based analysis of the volume sales change for the month of February 2024, adding more granularity to the previous segment's broader retail sales analysis.

text: Non-food stores sales volumes (the total of department, clothing, household and other non-food stores) rose by 0.7% over the month to February 2024, but fell 0.5% over the year.
analysis question: What is the change in sales volumes for non-food stores in February 2024, and how does it compare to the yearly change?
analysis operation: calculate the percentage change in sales volumes for non-food stores over the month and over the year to February 2024
logic description: The segment focuses on a specific subset of the retail category—non-food stores—and provides a comparison of sales volume change over the month and over the year, adding further detailed insight following the analysis of different retail categories in the previous segment.

text: Most of the increase within non-food stores was because of a monthly rise of 1.7% within clothing stores, following recent monthly falls. Retailers reported that new collections and promotions contributed to this rise.

Sales volumes at department stores and other non-food stores also grew over the month (by 1.6% and 0.4%, respectively). However, household goods stores fell by 1.0% with respondents reporting the economic climate and poor weather as factors that contributed to the fall.

The Met Office climate summaries reported a mild but wet February 2024 with generally unsettled weather. Southern England received 239% of its average rainfall and in this area, it was the wettest February on record (from 1836).
Largest monthly rise in online sales since July 2023

The amount spent online, known as online spending values, rose by 2.1% over the month to February 2024 (2.2% over the year). This monthly rise was the largest since July 2023 when shoppers switched to online shopping because of poor weather and increased promotions.
Clothing retailers reported strong online sales while department stores and household goods stores were the only two subsectors where sales values fell over the month.
This monthly increase in online sales led to a rise in the proportion of sales made online, from 25.1% in January 2024 to 25.7% in February 2024.
analysis question: What is the trend in online spending values and the proportion of sales made online in February 2024?
analysis operation: calculate the percentage changes in online spending values and the percentage shares of total sales for online retail in February 2024
logic description: This analysis builds on the previous segments' focus on retail sales by providing more details on the specific trend of online retail sales for the month of February 2024.
